==English==

===Etymology===
Italian, plural of ''[[salame]]'', salami. From ''[[sale]]'' “[[salt]]”, from Latin ''[[sal]]''.

===Pronunciation===
*:Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-ɑːmi|-ɑːmi]]

===Noun===
'''salami''' {{uncountable}}

# A highly [[season]]ed type of large [[sausage]] of [[Italian]] origin, typically made from chopped [[pork]] or [[beef]] and often [[garlic]], and served in slices.
# {{baseball}} A [[grand slam]]

